Daily menu of an obese child: don't breakfast and dinner stuffed
Over one third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have overweight problems, where overweight affects 9 per cent of the school population and obesity at 5%.
Obese children come from most families with a life-style that is not healthy, according to current research.
The importance of the environment where it grows for healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as reference, is demonstrated again.
At the table, for example, obsessive children are fed at least twice as often as children of normal-weighted families.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten fried potatoes the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program "obesity is not an accident".
In overweight families, there is no custom to practice sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey conducted in 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of last year's school year and participated in the same almost 900 basic education children from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not an accident", which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from 4th to 8th.
A proper and healthy diet in the family are determining factors that significantly reduce the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five daily meals according to the scheme: breakfast, lunch, food, breakfast and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," she collects one of the results of the survey.
No breakfast, but with a bowl for dinner
Experts warn that in healthy development, details are also important, such as having a fixed time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23 per cent of schoolchildren have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one breakfasts alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of the homes nothing breakfasts.
Breakfast is, however, the basis for a proper daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, much more often fried potatoes are consumed.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily fresh sweets (70%).
In general, more than 40 per cent of children surveyed sport, however, among their parents, this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled selected horses (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 colleges) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of a healthy diet, are far from ideal."
Among their favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is especially alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," the final study report warns.
As main food, the palm is taken pasta and closely followed by the meat of birds.
In practice, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to healthy habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive accurate information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who filled the questionnaire after the end of the prevention program "Obsity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases an important change in favor of the principles of healthy nutrition," the results of the study are noted.
Call attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would start to prefer normal and regular water.
Children would also choose more frequently in the questionnaire the meat of birds and fish for the main food and would restrict the consumption of sweet food and the derivatives of flour.
