The choirs at the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Terciopel Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festival of Academics.
During the same period, twenty corals will be presented from secondary and university centres.
The festival revolves around two concerts on 17 November.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the Coral of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the director Václav Hampl," said the organization's head, Jakub Čaloun.
The festival's summit is the free entrance for all audiences to the secondary choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program has the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Rožička and his Jazz Mass Celebration.
The concert "Students of Terciopelo" will be held at the venues of the Municipal House in Vynohrady, where university choirs will participate, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The Academic Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day and remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopel Revolution, but also to present coral music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Coral Union in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the head of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to festive concerts, a whole range of musical events, improvised shows by students and morning concerts.
